<div class="card" style="display:flex; align-items:center; align-items:center; gap:20px;">
🌱 <div><b>Crop Rotation</b><br>Crop rotation is the practice of planting different types of crops in the same area across sequential seasons. Instead of growing the same plant (monoculture), which drains the soil of specific nutrients, you rotate crops to keep the land "balanced" and healthy.</div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:20px;">
💧 <div><b>Irrigation</b><br>Proper watering, or irrigation, is the controlled application of water to crops to ensure they get the right amount of moisture at the right time. The goal is to provide enough water for growth without wasting resources or drowning the roots.</div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:20px;">
🌿 <div><b>Organic Compost</b><br>Organic compost is decomposed organic matter- like food scraps, leaves, and manure-that has been broken down by microorganisms. Often called "Black Gold," it is used to enrich soil and help plants thrive without synthetic chemicals.</div>
</div>

<div class="card" style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:20px;">
🐞 <div><b>Pest Control</b><br>Pest control in farming is the strategic management of organisms-like insects, weeds, fungi, and rodents- that damage crops and reduce harvests. The goal is rarely to "kill everything," but rather to manage pest populations so they don't cause significant economic damage while keeping the ecosystem healthy.</div>
</div>

